    "@id": "https://anchorfact.org/fact/fact-computer-science-001",
    "text": "Linux file permissions use a 3-tier model: Owner, Group, Others — each with Read (r=4), Write (w=2), Execute (x=1) permissions. Permission bits: `rwxr-xr--` means owner can read/write/execute, group can read/execute, others can read. `chmod 755 file` sets these numerically.",
